description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic, self-motivated and hardworking person to join our Pharmacy Portering team based at the Royal Glamorgan Hospital. You will carry out a whole range of Pharmacy Logistics and Portering duties and you will be expected to work effectively as part of a dedicated team. You should be willing to work in a flexible manner and be able to undertake the full remit of the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The main duties will be the delivery of drugs, IV Fluids, Controlled drugs and any other Pharmacy items to our wards. You will participate in a stock top up service for pharmacy items at ward level as well as compiling stock orders. It will also involve supporting other areas of Logistics including storekeeping when required.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Applicants must have experience of working in a healthcare environment as well as experience of distribution/stock control systems and should possess excellent communication and organisation skills. Applicants must also have an accurate and methodical approach to tasks as well as being conscientious, responsible and reliable, and have the ability to work off their own initiative as well as part of a team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Weekend working will be integral to this role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 10th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lisa Mahoney, Pharmacy Logistics Manager&lt;br /&gt;lisa.mahoney@wales.nhs.uk&lt;br /&gt;01443 443143&lt;/p&gt;
